
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Sikkim";
}
<link href="~/Script/StatesCss/sikkim.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<div class="main-container">
    <!-- BACKGROUND IMAGE -->
    <div id="top-section-main">

        <div id="top-section-content">
            <h1> Gangtok </h1>
            <h2> Sikkim </h2>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- PLACES TO VISIT SECTION -->
    <div id="feature-section">
        <h1 class="feature-section-title"> The top places to visit in <i>Sikkim</i></h1>
        <div class="feature-content">
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/pelling.jpg">
                <h3> Pelling </h3>
                <p> It is an old monastery which has been standing tall since 1705. It is one of the most famous shrines in West Sikkim and a must visit when in the region. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/nathulapass.jpg">
                <h3> Nathula Pass </h3>
                <p> The Nathula Pass has played a crucial role in strengthening the economy of India and has also helped in improving the border relations with China. It also plays a very significant role in the Sino-Indian trade. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/tsomgolake.jpg">
                <h3> Tsomgo Lake </h3>
                <p> Tsomgo Lake is known for its legendary beauty. In winter the lake remains frozen solid with the area around it covered in snow. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/yuksom.jpg">
                <h3> Yuksom </h3>
                <p> For the Bhutia community of Sikkim, Yuksom has special religious and cultural significance. It has a number of famous Buddhist monasteries and historical monuments as well as ancient Gorkhas small Village.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- MAP SECTION -->
    <div id="showcase1-container">
        <div class="showcase">
            <div class="cols-2">
                <iframe class="showcase1-pic" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d905182.2051965691!2d87.90665964756055!3d27.597622078133657!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39e6a56a5805eafb%3A0xa4c4b857c39b5a04!2sSikkim!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1618390547139!5m2!1sen!2sin" width="600" height="450" style="border:0;" allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-2">
                <div class="feature-text">
                    <h1 class="section-title">
                        Facts of Sikkim
                    </h1>
                    <p class="section-content">
                        <ul class="section-content-list">
                            <li>
                                In 1976, Sikkim became the 22<sup>nd</sup> state of India.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                In 2015, Sikkim became the 1<sup>st</sup> organic state of India.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Sikkim has over 552 different species of birds and about 690 species of butterflies.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The state has 28 mountain peaks, and has more than 80 glaciers.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Sikkim is one of the few states of India which receives regular snowfall.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div id="feature-section2">
        <h1 class="feature-section2-title">
            More about <i>Sikkim.. </i>  <br><br>
        </h1>
        <div class="slideshow">
            <div class="mySlides">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/sikkim.jpg" width="900" height="450" style="width:100%;">
                <div class="caption"> State : Sikkim</div>
            </div>
            <div class="mySlides">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/gangtokk.jpg" width="900" height="450" style="width:100%;">
                <div class="caption"> State's Capital : Gangtok</div>
            </div>
            <div class="mySlides">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/4districts.jpg" width="900" height="450" style="width:100%;">
                <div class="caption"> No. of districts of State : 4</div>
            </div>
            <div class="mySlides">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/gangtook.jpg" width="900" height="450" style="width:100%;">
                <div class="caption"> State's largest district : Gangtok </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mySlides">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Sikkim/englishnepali.jpg" width="900" height="450" style="width:100%;">
                <div class="caption"> State's official language : English & Nepali</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:center">
            <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(1)"></span>
            <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(2)"></span>
            <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(3)"></span>
            <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(4)"></span>
            <span class="dot" onclick="currentSlide(5)"></span>
        </div>
        <br><br>
        <a href="#" class="BookTicketBtn" style="text-align:center; margin:auto;"> BOOK YOUR TICKETS TODAY!! </a>
        <script>
                    var slideIndex = 0;
                    showSlides();

                    function showSlides() {
                    var i;
                    var slides = document.getElementsByClassName("mySlides");
                    var dots = document.getElementsByClassName("dot");
                    for (i = 0; i < slides.length; i++) {
                        slides[i].style.display = "none";
                    }
                    slideIndex++;
                    if (slideIndex > slides.length) {slideIndex = 1}
                    for (i = 0; i < dots.length; i++) {
                        dots[i].className = dots[i].className.replace(" active", "");
                    }
                    slides[slideIndex-1].style.display = "block";
                    dots[slideIndex-1].className += " active";
                    setTimeout(showSlides, 2500); // Change image every 2.5 seconds
                    }
        </script>
    </div>
